I am open to tutoring college mathematics and statistics courses that I am not currently teaching or a TA for. 
Please contact me for my rates and availability via email: [eleanor.waiss@colorado.edu](mailto:eleanorwaiss@colorado.edu)

**Past Experience**
I have tutored college math courses since being a student at Butler University, covering everything 
from Algebra 1 through the entire calculus sequence, linear algebra (my favorite!), and statistical theory; 
and electives like real analysis, modern algebra, and differential equations on an as-need basis. 
Having worked both 1-on-1 and in small group, I had the pleasure to serve as the tutoring 
coordinator my senior year in undergrad, overseeing the math department's tutor lab. I've also worked
as a private tutor for students at Purdue University, Indiana University-Indianapolis, and the
Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology.